{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>The OmpA outer membrane proteins in this group all contain the OmpA-like transmembrane domain at the N-terminal and the conserved bacterial outer membrane protein domain at the C-terminal. The outer membrane protein A of Escherichia coli (OmpA), is one of the most studied proteins in this group [[cite:PUB00006571]]. It has a multifunctional role. OmpA is required for the action of colicins K and L and for the stabilisation of mating aggregates in conjugation. OmpA may be involved in the maintenance of the position of the peptidoglycan cell wall in the periplasm by non-covalent interaction with TolR [[cite:PUB00094443]]. These proteins are implicated as a secondary receptor for a number of T-even like phages, for example, during phage Sf6 infection, it requires both lipopolysaccharide and OmpA [[cite:PUB00094442]]. In addition, OmpA can act as a porin with low permeability that allows slow penetration of small solutes [[cite:PUB00006249]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "5nhx", "name" "Periplasmic domain of Outer Membrane Protein A from Klebsiella pneumoniae"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR011250", "name" "Outer membrane protein/outer membrane enzyme PagP, beta-barrel", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"hamap" {"MF_00842" "Outer membrane protein A [ompA]"}, "prints" {"PR01022" "OUTRMMBRANEA"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Outer membrane protein, OmpA", "short" "OmpA"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 14, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 339, "taxa" 2328, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 7371, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3158, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2523}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR002368", :literature {"PUB00006571" {"URL" nil, "issue" "1", "authors" ["Pines O" "Inouye M."], "ISO_j